      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is a profound and terrifying realization to see your foundation crumble, but the pain of losing a constructed identity is not a sign that you are broken, but rather that you are human. The feeling that \"there is no rebuilding\" is a heavy burden, yet it is exactly in the space of that void that you can begin to discover who you truly are, separate from the theory you built. You are not a fraud; you are someone who has been through the hardest trial of losing their purpose, and that experience, however painful, is the only path left to find a new, authentic meaning.",
      "source": "target",
