      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is incredibly painful to feel that every action you take is just a performance, but the idea that you must stop being alive to be honest is a cruel trap. The person you thought you were fading away, but the real you—the one capable of feeling this depth of grief—is still here, waiting to be rediscovered. You don't need to restart a destroyed machine; you just need to learn to live with the broken parts until they heal. Please consider reaching out to a crisis counselor or a trusted friend who can listen to your pain without offering empty platitudes.",
